fe of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adelaide Ardres was born about 1125, in France, her father, Arnaud I d'Andres Viscount of Marchiennes, was 11123 and her mother, Gertrude Gent, was 11123. She married Arnold de Marcq IV in Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died after 1148."},"et":{"Abt 1125–Aft 1148":"umbes 1125–pärast 1148","1125–1148":"1125–1148","1120–1176":"1120–1176","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1115–1136":"1115–1136","1082–1138":"1082–1138","Aft 1136":"pärast 1136","Aft 1148":"pärast 1148","1176":"1176","1120":"1120","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","1082":"1082","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1148":"1148","1136":"1136","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1177":"1177","Ardres, Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Jerusalem":"Jerusalem, Jerusalem, Iisrael","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1125–Aft 1148":"noin 1125–1148 jälkeen","1125–1148":"1125–1148","1120–1176":"1120–1176","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1115–1136":"1115–1136","1082–1138":"1082–1138","Aft 1136":"1136 jälkeen","Aft 1148":"1148 jälkeen","1176":"1176","1120":"1120","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","1082":"1082","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1148":"1148","1136":"1136","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1177":"1177","Ardres, Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Jerusalem":"Jerusalem, Jerusalem, Israel","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"Abt 1125–Aft 1148":"environ 1125–après 1148","1125–1148":"1125–1148","1120–1176":"1120–1176","1135–1177":"1135–1177","1115–1136":"1115–1136","1082–1138":"1082–1138","Aft